<view version="2.0">
    
    <panel id="projMngActsInfo_info" type="html" dataSource="none" showOnLoad="true">
        <html><h1 style="font-size:14px">Project Actions and Service Requests</h1>
        <p style="font-size:11px">Review and edit project actions.*  Create Service Requests for actions.
        </p>        
        <ul style="font-size:11px">
        		<li><b>Update Selected Actions: </b>Update multiple Action Items.  For example, to mark items as Complete, select the completed items and click "Update Selected".  In the dialog window, set the status to "Completed" and enter the Date Completed.  The status update will be saved for all selected items.  Note: Rejected and Requested Change Orders will not be updated.  Update Actions will not overwrite pre-existing Date Completed values.</li>
					  <li><b>Add: </b>Add a new Action Item to the Project.</li>
					  <li><b>Show More Fields/Show Less: </b>Show additional fields including Action location and description.</li>									
            <li><b>Copy Baseline Costs: </b>Available for Actions without specified Design Costs.  Select items and click "Copy Baseline Costs" to copy over the Baseline Cost estimates to the Design Cost.</li>
					  <li><b>Export to MS Project: </b>Export Actions to MS Project.  Actions which are Requested, Planned, Scheduled or In Progress are included in the export.</li>
					  <li><b>Import from MS Project: </b>Import Actions from an MS Project file.  You will have a chance to review changes before finalizing the import.</li>	
					  <li><b>Service Requests: </b>Click on the Service Request icon to view existing Service Requests created for that Action.  To create a Service Request for an Action, open the Edit Action dialog and select "Create Service Request".</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="font-size:11px">* Actions receive a check mark when they are Completed, Closed or 100% Complete.</p>       
        </html>
    </panel>
</view>
